      <title>Man dies after falling into meat mincing machine in Malaysia.</title>
      <description><![CDATA[MASJID TANAH, MALAYSIA <br/> A man unfortunately had to meet his maker after having an accident at a meat factory in Malaysia. <br/>According to the Star, a 47-year-old Nepalese worker was involved in the incident at a meat processing facility near Masjid Tanah. <br/>An official from the Malacca fire department said that the man was doing maintenance with three other workers in the morning at the factory on December 30. <br/>For some reason during the check, the meat-mincing machine suddenly turned on and caught the man at his waist.<br/><br/>The Star reported the other workers called for emergency crews at 7:45 a.m. and authorities arrived on the scene in under 10 minutes. <br/><br/>He unfortunately succumbed to his injuries on the spot.  <br/>The Star also said that it took the Masjid Tanah Fire and Rescue Department around 30 minutes to extricate the guy.   <br/>An investigation is being launched into the incident. <br/><br/>State news agency Bernama reported that around 360,000 Nepalese are working in Malaysia, with most of them doing security, construction or hospitality jobs.]]></description>
